String formatting
----------------
See strformat.py

We can also interchange positional parameters.

s=s.format(,age=50,who="She")

color=["brown","blue","grey","red"]
0 will be pointing to colour.
s="his eyes are {0[1]} and hair is {0[2]}"
s=s.format(color)

d=dict(animal="elephant",wt=12000)
"The {0[animal]} weighs {0[wt]} kg".format(d)

d=dict(animal="elephant",wt=12000)---doesn't work
"The {0[0} weighs {0[1]} kg".format(d)
--------------------

unic="ಇಈ"
"{0!s} {0!a}".format(unic)

s-printing in string format
a-printing in ASCII format

----------------------
Outputting in a certian format

:     fill              align        sign       #(bin,dec..)       0(pad no)     width.precision(min width).(how many digits shown aftr decimal)      type(extensions like short,long...)
     Any             
     char
     exception
     }

shared on moodle.

s="The sword of truth"
"{0}".format(s)

s="The sword of truth"
"{0:25}".format(s)

25-min field width

s="The sword of truth"
"{0:>25}".format(s)

s="The sword of truth"
"{0:^25}".format(s)

s="The sword of truth"
"{0.10}".format(s)

.followed by digit is max width

s="The sword of truth"
maxwd=12
"{0}".format(s[:maxwd])

s="The sword of truth"
"{0:.{1}}".format(s,maxwd)

Integers
--------------------------
"{0:012}".format(8984383)


