Tuples
--------
ordered sequence of zero or more object reference.
slicing and striding are same

creation

emp=tuple()
t=("neo",96,-54,6.787)
usage of paranthesis is not mandatory
print(t[2])

Functions

t.index(element)

Tuples dont have find method
print(t[2][1])

Tuples in tuple
-----------------

hair=('blck','blue','green')
eye=('black','blue','brown')

pair=(hair,eye)


things=(4,8.9,('green',('123','pQr'),'list'))
things[2][1][1][1]


manufacturer,model,seating=(0,1,2)
MIN,MAX=(0,1)

aircraft=("Airlindia","A380",(100,250))
aircraft[seating][MAX]

Sequence unpacking

a=("v",5,9)
b=("a",6,3)

a,b=(b,a)

for x,y in((3,4),(5,12),(28,45)):
    print(math.hypot(x,y))
    
